#!/usr/local/projects/routing/help/html_filter.pl
<h2 align=center>Help for the "Optimize" section of route ordering</h2>
The "Optimize" section is an <b><i>un</i></b>ordered list of stops that
the driver will make after performing all the stops in the "Start with"
section but before all the stops in the "End with" section.
It will never include the distribution center.
<p>Although displayed in the order the computer considers the best guess
when the menu is drawn, the software may re-order this list as
required by conditions when the route sheet is created.
<p>
<b><i>Note</i></b>:  All new stops that have not been otherwise ordered yet
appear in this section.  Unless there is some compelling reason otherwise
(such as having to make somebody a first stop because they will then leave
for kidney dialysis), it is best to leave patrons in this section and allow
the software to create the most efficient route.
